Here's one from the "aerial Old Spot" category: according to Kotaku, the Xbox 360 is "so sold out that Microsoft Japan actually put out an official statement about the situation in The Land of the Rising Sun, apologizing for the lack of consoles. Since demand has eclipsed supply, Microsoft's supply has gone totally dry. The company is ramping up production, and the console will not be shipped to stores until next month."Xbox has famously flopped in Japan, and the sudden turnaround seems to be the result of the popularity of Namco Bandai's new role-playing game Tales of Vesperia, an Xbox exclusive, which almost quadrupled sales. According to AFP:This probably won't last.....